column4: I didn't ask because you seem like someone who is careful about privacy. Also this is Andrew, also this is the second time sending this message. I thoroughly confused a stranger just moments ago. 7887 not 7877
Bwahahahaha
Yeah, well, I offered so it's okay that you have my number now.
Hey, how about the Palladium at 9? Or did you guys really want to do the Silverado?
I don't mind when or where. I can pass that on. I'm still waiting for a response from Kelli/Reggie. They're both at work lol so I have to wait for them to by on break.
Okay. I was just thinking if we did the Palladium then we could eat somewhere around there too.
BJs Restaurant at 8? Is that cool? Kelli suggested it.
Sounds perfect.
745 actually. 8 might be cutting it close unless we inhale the food.
Haha either way is fine.
Ok these people -_- lol. Do you like Chik fil a?
Haha sure
8 ish. Reggie has to drive home before he gets to my place.
Okay
I'm still waiting on Reggie. Did you find Kelli?
Is it okay if I just meet you guys at the theater?
Sure
I'm not at chik fil a.
Sorry. I got caught up with family stuff. But I'll still be there.
It's ok. See you there.
Hey last night was really fun. Totally should have gone to bed earlier though. I don't know how you've managed two 3-hour nights in a row.
Last night was fun, yes. Very fun. I'm glad you invited me. And as far as sleep goes, maybe that's my superpower. Haha. But no, I am pretty tired. Next time we'll go to bed earlier haha
Are there any cult classic movies you haven't seen? Would you want to have a movie marathon sometime?
A movie marathon would be awesome! I'm sure there are many many movies I haven't seen haha  if you made a list I could say if I have or not.
And you still owe me a board game night!
Haha I thought we were gonna have people to play last night! Everyone bailed!
It was still fun though. And maybe a board game night would be good if it started earlier and dinner came along with the games. We can try that another time.
I like how last night we kind of inadvertently sent Kelli and Rick on a dinner date at Chik Fil A lol.
Hahahaha yeah we did
I didn't even realize that haha
Have they said anything about that yet?
About the status of their "relationship"?
Or Espelien dinner?
Haley all my gosh seriously Siri
*us bailing. Siri is so stupid lol. Either that or I'm just bad at speaking. Which is definitely true sometimes.
Do you have tomorrow off?
I mean, after church and everything.
You can come over too. I'm pretty sure Kris's girlfriend is hanging out with us too. We could watch Ishtar! =D
Hahaha okay. What time?
Uh...
That's a good question.
Haha you can just let me know when you figure it out.
Prolly sometime during midday. I want to make cupcakes!
Haha okay. Cupcakes sound good! Let me know if I should bring anything. Movies or food related.
You could bring shows or something.
Any preference?
Old shows? Idk lol what do you have?
Cartoons or what?
What do you like?
Pretty much anything. I have a wide variety of movies, and a lot of them.
Do you want me to just get a handful together and you all can pick from that?
Bring stuff you don't mind watching again.
Haha that's everything I own! I don't buy it unless I've seen it and would watch it again. I'm a snob that way lol
So you don't get board =P
I won't be bored lol
Haha each movie I own has a time cycle associated with it. I can't rewatch it until a certain amount of time has passed haha.
I'm like that with some movies, but not many haha
Some movies have shorter cycles than others. Like Inception is a year, and Jurassic Park is like 3 hours.
Hahahaha did you watch it again on Friday after I left? Lol
I was tempted. Haha ok maybe not really 3 hours. But I have prolly seen that movie at least a few hundred times in my life.
Just like Airplane. When I was in highschool I would watch that movie every single night when I went to bed.
That's a lot of viewings lol
I don't think I have a movie like that. But I do have lots that I've seen several dozen times.
I family had a TV growing up so I guess I had that advantage. When did you finally get a TV?
I showed Kris MST3K Pod People tonight. You really have to see it.
When I was 14 lol
Do you like Mystery Science Theatre?
I've only seen one or two episodes but I liked what I've seen.

Hey Kris and his gf arent coming over till around 7, but you can come over now if you want. I was thinking about making cupcakes or cookies or some other sugary wonder lol. Matt was talking about baking things yesterday and it got me in the baking mood.
Haha okay. I'm having lunch with my Dad and then I'll hear over. Okay?
I'll let you know when I'm headed that way. I already have the movie options with me too haha
Ok, omg do you like Cream Puffs? O_O enjoy your lunch, I'll keep from bothering you while you're out lol.
You're not bothering me haha. And yes, cream puffs are awesome!
Is it okay for me to head your way? Just finished lunch with my Dad.
Yeah, I'm starting cream puffs! lol
116 is the call code.
*gate
Haha okay. I'll be there shortly.
Happy late Easter lol.
You too!
Happy Easter, that is.
Haha yeah I understood.
Just making sure. I can get somewhat incoherent at times. Especially when I'm tired.
You're not driving are you?
No. I just got home
Ok. Just making sure. Otherwise I would have had to scold you.
Now get some sleep lol.
Haha no scolding necessary. And I will. I'm already about to fall into bed.
Night!
Buonanotte!
üòä
üé∂Cruising on down main street, you're relaxing, feeling goodüé∂ \LFyou've got the theme song stuck in my head haha
lol. I've been singing the Ishtar songs.
I have to say, that movie was pretty awesome! I've been asking people all day if they've seen it lol
Thanks for sharing it with me. My life is slightly more complete hahaha
I don't think I even laughed that hard when I saw it the first time lol.
I got the closing team to do a 1 2 3 Hail Hydra!
Well I certainly laughed pretty hard. What made it funnier this time?
And that's awesome by the way. Hail Hydra!
It was funnier because you were laughing a much. I didn't think you were going to like it lol.
Well I loved it! It deserves many more viewings for sure. I love to laugh. Why didn't you think I'd like it? Haha
Idk I'm not 100% on your movie preferences yet.
I don't know that I am either haha
I like a wide variety of stuff.
But Ishtar is definitely on my list now!
So thanks for that!
My mom ate one of your cream puffs and thought it came from a bakery lol
They were also very good.
=D thanks. I do cookies too. But those require a lot of focus lol.
You've mentioned that haha. I do pies and truffles lol
And crumbles and mousses too. I almost forgot.
Aww.. I can't eat pies. lol
Why?
I have trouble eating fruit. Super intense gag reflex.
Especially when it's been cooked so it's soft
I meant pumpkin pie. Lol. Do you eat that?
I don't know if I've ever tried it. Ive basically just tried to stay away from pies my whole life because I just assume they'll make me gag. Except chocolate ones.

Haha well I never ate a pumpkin pie until four years after I had started baking the recipe I make. And it's the only pumpkin pie I'll eat. It's not chunky, almost more like cheesecake or an icebox pie.
But I don't like cheesecake, so I'm just going off what people tell me haha
lol
I prefer cakes anyway.
Cakes are Wesome
Awesome
Haha
Yes they are
What's your favorite cake flavor?
I think just chocolate. I'm not a fan of dark chocolate though.
Best answer possible! Hahaha
Only chocolate for me too lol
Would you be interested in joining me on a "explore a new church" adventure sometime?
Also do you like ice cream? lol
Yes and yes
Hahaha
You make me smile. It's nice.
üòÅ
Haha. I keep trying to convince myself to get up and go somewhere but it's nerve racking when you're alone. =\
And ice cream is super hard to eat.
It's painful lol.
Yeah, trying new churches is hard for me too. Did you have one in mind? I was thinking of trying Bandera Road Christian Church.
Hahaha why is it painful? And what about frozen yogurt?
I don't really have any in mind. Usually when I can talk myself into going I just find a random one nearby and go. Not a very well thought out approach haha.
Haha maybe that's why it hasn't been successful
And as for ice cream, i think my mouth is just super sensitive to temperatures.
Mine is too. Haha so I have to eat it slowly.
How was your day?

I did some sales planners for the first time ever. That was fun. I just right this second picked up a spider that was descending from the ceiling right in front of me. What about you? Anything eventful?
Lunch of over, if I don't reply that's why.

Yeah I liked doing sales planners but it was hard for me to feel productive with them because I always kept getting pulled away from them every five seconds, so it took forever. \LFNot much happened at work. I decorated the break room for a special lunch we had today haha. And I bought tickets to a concert in Austin that my sister and I are going to. So that's cool. Haha okay, well have a good night at work then. Text me when you can.
What's the concert?
Birdy and Christina Perri
I'm wanting to see Birdy mostly.
I've never heard of Birdy. I do know who Christina Perri is though.
She's a really young singer/songwriter from Britain who plays the piano. Very indie.
They've got some really cool outfits in her wings video
You looked her up? Hahaha
Find her version of "Skinny Love" if you can. It's really pretty.
wow.. That was kinda sad.
Hahaha it's been a rough year for me lol
I mostly like what she does with her voice. The tone is really pretty. I try to ignore the words and just listen to the melody I guess
She does have quite a voice.
Yeah. She's only like 15 or so.
That's amazing to me.
Waht??
Superhuman
Okay, no, she's 17 now. But she released her first album at 15. Started recording it at 14.
She's still young. I always wondered high school aged people manage an entertainment career at scuba young age.
*such haha
Yes scuba is hard at a young age lol
Scuuuuuuba
Hahaha
Yeah I know what you mean.
It's crazy to see how early some people get started in their careers. But, maybe that's partly why they are so successful, because of the shock factor and what-not.
Who knows... Either way, I really like her voice.
And it should be fun. I haven't been to a concert in I don't know how long.
Years. Many many years. Haha

I don't know if I've ever even been to a real concert lol. I was supposed to go see Owl City in DC a couple years ago but the person in charge of getting the tickets waited too long and it sold out. But she didn't tell me this till after I had gotten my ticket to fly to DC. Haha
Oh man. Did you at least enjoy DC? The Smithsonian is pretty awesome!
On top of that once that weekend rolled around, most of us were sick and we spent the weekend doing things sick people shouldn't do like hiking and sledding down snowless hills.
That sounds fun!
We spent no time in DC haha. We were so sick. I had developed a horrible sinus infection by the time I had to fly back. It was a very interesting weekend.
And feverish and such. There was a lot of delirious wanderings.
I used to do silly stuff like play in the snow in my bathing suit, so I understand the delirious wanderings lol
What? Why? Weren't you cold? Did you get sick all the time?
Haha because it was fun lol
Touch√©
And this was at what age? Lol
It was cold but you got used to it. And no, I never got sick from that lol
8-14. When I lived in places that snowed lol
I was always very careful as a child but I would get sick every few months and it would last forever! That is until I got those thingies in my mouth removed. Then I stopped getting sick so often.
Yeah I got strep every year at least twice. But I guess I was a little more carefree in those days lol
Hey, when are you going to Seattle again?
Uh..
One sec
The 16th is when I end up in Seattle
Haha okay
My plans changed. I'm there from the 12th-18th.
Are you serious???
Overlap!!
Haha
Haha yeah. I'm serious.
Are you going to be free at all though?

Yes. I'm going without my friend now. So I get to explore and see family on my own. My sister might go with me, but that's not final yet. And I already bought the ticket, so either way I'm going. Haha
So, yeah, I'll be free.
We'll have to meet up!
Yeah?
That would be fun!
Are you going to actually be IN Seattle? Or an outlying city?
In the city. I'll be staying with my Aunt. She lives downtown. But everything is pretty close up there.
I'm going to be in DuPont, but I'm planning on making trips to Seattle to see stuff.
Well, if you need someone to do stuff with just let me know haha
I definitely will.
So I got an odd compliment today.
Which was?
I was at a register and this man told me I had impeccable enunciation. Haha. Then he said, "You're not from around here are you?"
Hahaha that's awesome
And you said "no, no I'm not" lol
I believe those were my exact words lol.
Taking extra care to pronounce the "t" and the end of "not"
*at the end
The after I told him my life story we started talking about the houses and beaches in Florida.
Was he from Florida as well?
He said he took a trip to St Pete recently
That's cool. I've never been to Florida.
It is pretty gorgeous there. But the humidity makes you want to slam your face into a brick wall.
What?! Bwahahahahaha
Ok maybe now that bad.
*not
That's pretty bad lol
I don't miss Florida very much. But I do miss the thunderstorms. So so much. Such beautiful monstrosities.
Last time I experienced anything close to a Florida storm was when I lived in Italy. And those still weren't as intense.
Yeah storms were fun growing up. I miss the clean smell of rain. It smells like cat pee when it rains here haha. We had lots of hurricane type winds with our storms in Washington. So that was crazy.
We don't get enough thunder here. It's so sappy! I need my thunder to knock dishes out of my cabinets!
The house rattling kind? Yeah, that's not here at all.
Even the rain is wimpy. It's depressing. I miss having four actual seasons. And snow. I really miss snow.
Do you want to move back to Washington someday?
I'd love to move back to the Northwest. I certainly don't want to stay here much longer. Just depends on what God's got in store for me.
I'd like to live somewhere Northern eventually. I'm not big on the hot and sunny scene.
Yeah me neither. I like sun, but I like being able to sit in the shade and have it cooler than sitting in the sun lol.
And these 100+ degree summers have been killing me slowly for years.
Where would you want to move?
I honestly don't know. I don't really feel like I have a home anywhere. I just want to be around people I care about.
That makes sense. I feel like the Northwest is my home, but my family is mostly down here so moving immediately would be difficult.
I've often thought about just picking a random place and going.
But it seems like they're all eventually migrating up to that corner of the U.S.
Like getting a map and pointing? Haha
That could be a valid way to pick a place to live I guess haha

Haha. Almost my entire family is in Florida. But my brother and I are not too fond of it. I think both of us have some "emotional scarring"? that happened around the time my parents and I left to move to GA. And over the years developed a lot of negative energy towards Florida. Am I getting to psychological now? lol
Haha no. I feel the same about Texas lol. Where does your brother love?
Hahaha whoops *live
He loves in Portland.
He also lives there.
Bwahahahaha. That's cool. Portland is awesome.
I miss those streets haha
And the food.
My brother is a cook... I miss having him here. For food AND 'cause I love him lol.
He did live with us in San Antonio for about a year. He moved here after lost his job.
And suddenly the creme puffs make so much more sense haha.
Ad he lived here for one year, hated it, and moved on as quickly as possible? Haha
*and

Basically. He had just gotten married. And when he lost his job they moved down here because they had no monies. Omg you would have loved my sister in law. When her and I were together the puns would not stop!
Hahaha puns are fun!
Ôøº
Hopefully you can zoom in lol
Haha I've seen that page before.
Yeah I've had it saved for a while lol. Too bad it wasn't anything new
Ôøº
Haha this was when I copied your number wrong.
Hahaha that's funny
There wasn't any additional response?
No =( I was so hoping for one too.
Yeah that would've been awesome.
Honestly though, I feel like I've met the person with that phone number lol
I think they worked with me at Hollister.
But I could be wrong.
Haha should I ask them if they ever worked at Hollister?
I remember being like "what? That's almost my number!"
Hmmm, if they never responded again then they were probably annoyed. And if it's the person I think it was, then her boyfriend probably wouldn't enjoy the weird messages.
It was either a Lauren or an Elena. And they were both not very nice girls.
Haha.
My cell number has a Columbus, GA area code. Let me tell you. I have gotten some weird wrong number calls and texts.
The texts are fun though because I can play along.
I have a tendency to not answer calls if I don't recognize the number, unless I'm expecting a call. And I've never gotten a weird text before.
Oh yeah I never answer calls unless I know who is calling. People leave messages on my voicemail though. Even after listening to my message. Haha.
Really? No one ever leaves me messages by mistake haha
I'm trying to figure out how to say this without sounding like a horrible person.
It's not a very educated local.
Locale
Georgia?
Columbus GA
Gotcha haha I thought you were planning on insulting me lol since you weren't sure how to "say something without sounding like a horrible person"
Oh no!
Hahaha
I was thinking "what must he think of me" lol
Maybe I should just jump right into what I'm about to say and apologize later. Whenever I preface something I tend to give the wrong idea lol.
That wouldn't have even needed an apology lol
You're too nice. Much nicer than most. But that's a good thing.
Thank you.
Of course.
You know you can tell me if and whenever you want to go to sleep right? I really don't want to infringe on your sleep.
Haha yeah I know. You can do the same though.
Rather than though, I should have said too
Hey I do though. lol
I do need to work on some homework though. And you should get some rest. You wake up earlier than I do.
Yeah I probably do haha
Well, good luck with the homework then and sorry to keep you from school.
It's been fun procrastinating with you haha. Goodnight.
Haha yeah it was worth missing out on some sleep lol. Night
That person worked at Hollister. O_O
You asked? Hahaha
You got me wondering. lol
Did it leave off there? Or are you still asking questions? Lol
I just left it there. Wasn't really sure what else to say after that. Should I? Haha
No haha leave it there. They all gossip a whole lot and if my name was brought up it could turn into stupidness. Haha
I would never drop your name. I respect your anonymity.
=P
Hahaha well thanks for that. It's up to you if you want to ask.
And yeah, I tend to stay pretty private.
But who knows, maybe you'll gain a new friend.
I think I'll hold off lol.
Hahahaha okay
How was class?
Or are you off today?

I spent the whole class on imgur. I really only went in to turn in my homework and pickup my exam. And I learned that my professor knows me by name. I asked him about the exams and he walked over to his pile and pulled mine out. I don't recall ever telling him my name. I don't even show up to half his classes. O_O

Haha I had a professor like that once too. I always read novels for my other classes during his lectures and one day he decided to call on me to answer a question. Fortunately, I can double task reasonably well so I had at least been following along. He thought he got me though, so he was disappointed when I argued a different point on the topic. Haha
Nice save.
I guess maybe they read our jakes everytime we turn something in.
Yeah I can be pretty smooth every once in a blue moon. Haha but usually I'm pretty awkward
Yeah that would make sense.
Awkward is good too though.
It makes for interesting stories.
So how's work?
And I have many of those interesting stories hahaha unfortunately.

Work is okay. I'm having to diffuse a couple of arguments between full grown adults this week. It's all really petty and shouldn't even be an issue, but since it's my job to manage them I have to is a way to get these groups of adults to treat eachother like adults and not children.
*find a way
Barney songs...
That sounds tough. Crowd controlling a dispute is not fun.
Yeah.... I guess. But I don't play the guitar so it couldn't be a real Kumbaya Fest either haha

I'm decent at crowd controlling, but it still gives me a headache. I don't know why people can't be nice to eachother and forgive others for their mistakes. So much in this world would be easier if we let go of our egos.
I've escaped my Texas license plate! Ôøº
So a Georgia phone number and a Florida license and license plate, but a Texas address. Hahaha
And Washington insurance!
Like butter scraped over too much bread.
You're feeling stretched thin?
I just wanted to fit a little LotR in there.
It was very smooth haha
Like... Butter?
Ha
Hahahahahaha
Very nice
Yes. Just like butter. And not the synthetic butter either. The handchurned smooth and creamy kind. Lol
The kind that Jedidiah used to slave over. Mmhmm that Bessy made some fine cream ya hear?
Bwahahahaha
I'm not sure where we're even going with this hahaha.
Yeah I don't know. Is it because you're craving toast? Lol
I do need to eat today. I should prolly do that.
Yes that would be advisable.
I just ate. Turkey sandwich. It was alright.
I just remembered I had that leftover stir fry. I wonder if it's any good. Oh well I'm about to find out.
Birds are tasty. And cute
You made it on Friday? Or Saturday?
Yes. They are tasty.
And often cute too.
I like owls.
I think Friday. Not 100% though. Owls are awesome.
It should be fine. Just microwave it. It'll nuke all the bacteria out hahaha
Yes. Owls are my favorite.
Weren't you getting on my case about hot fuzz? Ôøº
Yes haha
I think I'm gonna get it. I don't have any of these yet.
DVDs are like collecting cards =)
I haven't seen the World' End, but Hot Fuzz is pretty funny, and Shaun of the Dead is awesome.
Yeah, I know what you mean. I have way too many movies lol
I was just told that world end is bad. Oh well lol.
Oh really? I bet you could find the other two by themselves for less than $20.
And, more importantly, can you trust that person's taste in movies? Haha
What do they think about Ishtar?

Doh I should have looked. Well at least I have 3 new movies to add to my server =D. It was everyone at the boat giving comments on the movies. Darrian, Reggie, and Stefon. I came into work to finish up some training paperwork.
Ah I see. What are you doing training paperwork for?
And you are one of I believe just two people I've showed Ishtar to.
Well I'm honored then haha. And thanks for sharing it with me.
They're making me complete learning plans for all my trainees now. It's weird. I've never had to do that before.
Are you at least getting paid to do the extra work?
*Cough cough* I was totally not working off the clock.
Andrew! That's illegal lol
Actually all I needed were two signatures.
I didn't really do any paperwork.
But were you working?
It was... Getting a signature on my way to the drop box?
Hahaha I'm not fully convinced
=D
Just don't make a habit of it. It's a hard habit to break. Trust me.
I'm serious! That's all I did. I'm not scheduled again till Saturday, but I really needed to get those in so I came up to say hi to Reggie and drop them off.
Haha fine fine
I know. I want a job where I don't have to worry about clocking in or working off the clock. I should be able to take care of things when I need too lol.
Yeah. That'll come soon enough.
You won't find anything like that in retail though haha
Speaking of taking care of things. How do you get anything done at work when you're texting me all day? Haha =) not that I don't love it.
I'm in an office and I multi-task really well lol
So I'm not having to walk around all day.
I want an office. Or a cubical.
Or a just a chair really.
Personally I'd go for an office, but I'm saying that because I have one lol
Haha what's your office look like?
Ummm it's big lol
Lots of wood furniture. Real plants and orchids and tons of photographs I took.
You should come visit me sometime lol
Do I need to make an appointment? lol
Haha no
Maybe I will.
Just text me ahead of time to make sure I'm there haha
My office is at one of the warehouses, but I'm in charge of three of them, so I travel between them a lot.
So if you're not working again till Saturday, do you have plans tomorrow evening?
Nothing concrete. Why would you like to do something?
Let me rephrase that. I am going to work on homework in the morning but I am free in the evening.
Haha yeah I would. And the evening would be perfect.
Did you have anything specific in mind?
Not yet. I can find something though, unless there's something you've been wanting to do.
I'm down for just about anything.
No preferences?
I'm sure anything you come up with will be fun. There's always movies and word games to fall back on.
Haha well I won't take the easy way out.
There's always building birdhouses lol.
Haha
Is that the newest hobby? Hahahaha
It just now popped into my head lol.
Haha fair enough
Is there any food you don't like?
Besides pie?
Hmm. Pickles?
Hahaha I meant type of food and you know it. Lol. Or is there some type of food or restaurant you've been wanting to try?
I have one part worked out already, but the food needs your input too lol
Haha I had a family friend invite us over for dinner once and she made meatloaf with large pickle chunks. Haha I always think of that when I get asked about what I don't eat.
The only thing I really ever have trouble eating is fruit and raw veggies.
Aside from salad I guess.
Although I don't know if that's considered a veggie.
More of a plant substance.
Hahaha yes salad is lots of veggies.
So nowhere you've been wanting to try?
What about ethnic foods? Anything a no go with that?
Nope, not that I can think of.
Hahaha you're not helping at all lol
Haha what exactly are you trying to get out of me? lol
Where you want to eat dinner lol
I don't want to pick somewhere and it's not at all what you'd want to eat
I like Chinese food, I like Mexican, BBQ in Texas is a little weird. But I'll eat anywhere. What do you like? Maybe we can narrow it down to some common shared flavours lol.

I will eat just about any type of food, but not beef, pork, or shellfish. Hahaha the flavor doesn't matter. That's why I was asking you, hahaha. Cause the spices aren't an issue for me. You haven't had any cravings recently?
Mexican and Asian stuff.
What about that?
Okay. See, that gives me something to start with lol
I could ask Thuy about good Asian places. She's always talking to me about food lol.
I've got a good list of places. Unless you don't trust me lol
I trust you.
Good.
My mom grew up in Asia. I know my Asian food. Lol
Now, does the type of Asian matter? Thai? Vietnamese? Chinese? Japanese?
I'm a little iffy on Viet.
Okay. The night has been planned.
I'll pick you up at 8?
If that's okay...
That sounds perfect. Is it a surprise? lol
If you're cool with that lol. I'm down for a kidnapping haha

The best time I've ever had was when I kidnapped my best friend in high school and took her to the zoo. She was blindfolded and had ear plugs in. It was epic. We took her all the way to the butterfly house where she felt them getting on her arms and started freaking out before we took off the blindfold. But I won't blindfold you. I won't be that weird haha
Unless you don't want it to be a surprise.
Haha that is exactly my kind of weird.
Haha really? Well good.
I'll find a good blindfold then lol
Still on for tonight?
Yeah. Sorry I was showering.
Yes I am.
Don't apologize for cleanliness haha. Will you be ready if I pick you up around 7:45?
I will be here ready to go.
Should I be worried about wearing certain clothing? Formal, warm, hazmat? Since I'm not aware of where or what we're doing lol.
Haha definitely hazmat
No, just a tshirt and jeans. Or whatever you're most comfortable in.
We can do hazmat another time lol
Haha, I've always wanted to tour Chernobyl.
That's would take a bit more notice than just a few hours though haha. I might be creative, but I don't think I'm that skilled yet.
*that
Still got the pink nails?
Uh somewhat lol. I got most of it off using cologne lol. I was so afraid I was going to reek of heavy cologne though.

I know when I was a kid I was really open about sharing how I felt, but when I got into fourth grade I was bullied pretty fiercely by girls all the way through high school, so I kind of shut down. \LF\LFIt was, and still is, hard for me to make friends and to know when it's okay to start opening up to people. So for me, it's due to the history I have with sharing too much and that being taken advantage of that I find it hard to relate to others. \LF\LFI suppose it's about protecting me. I will compartmentalize a lot of what I feel and often will think that I feel a certain way about something or someone, and then when I'm more comfortable with the situation my feelings about it change completely. So, in a way I almost don't allow myself the opportunity to fully experience or appreciate something or someone because I'm so busy being guarded and keeping my feelings stored away in neat and tidy little drawers in my brain. \LF\LFI'm aware that I do this, but I've been doing it for so long it would probably be incredibly difficult to change that behavior. My ex always said I was very cold. Which I know isn't the case, but I think what he was trying to say was that I didn't share my feelings, so it made it seem like I didn't have any, good or bad or anything in between. \LF\LFAnd there's also how awkward I am...I don't pick up on verbal cues so I often misunderstand other people and their feelings or intentions as well. So if a person isn't willing to be patient with me and allow me to ask a lot of odd questions most other people wouldn't ask, then I tend to frustrate them and they lose interest in cultivating a friendship with me. \LF\LFI'm an oddball, not in a bad way, but I ask a lot of questions to help me understand where a person is coming from, and not many people like such intrusive and inquisitive behavior. So that's my take on the whole situation.

"Do not speak anything you wouldn't write in permanent ink, and do not write anything you wouldn't want published for the public to read." \LFIt's just a concept I've come across over the years I've worked as a manager. I've heard things similar to this phrase, but I tweaked it and made it my own. I feel that it's very important on both a professional, and more importantly, a personal level. And it's very strongly how I feel about the relationships I have: that not only should I treat others how I want to be treated, but that I should treat them in a way that I would treat them if I were in the limelight and being analyzed by the rest of the world. So basically, don't live by the golden rule, live like the world is watching your every move. And don't say or do things you wouldn't want to be held accountable for at a later time. I think I put it on the board in my office because I was having a particularly bad day of nasty text messages from my ex and I wanted to remind myself to remain cool, calm, and collected. It's a character from a Legend of Zelda game named Kaffei. It's a long side story in the game that most people don't play through due to it's length and complexity. I love the story of though, I'll give you a little summary. You can skip it if you want. \LF\LFIt follows the story of this guy, Kaffei. He had fallen in love with this girl named Anju who runs an inn in the town they live in. They decided to get engaged.(Masks are a very core part of this game. Almost everyone has a mask that is symbolic of they're character.) They make a promise that on the dawn of they're wedding day they would fuse they're masks together into one as symbol of their love for each other.(Kinda like a "two shall become of one flesh" type thing.) Anyway, days before their wedding day someone cursed him to look like a child(Kinda looks like he's 10-12 now.). Seeking help, he attempts to meet with someone who he thinks can change him back. Instead he is ambushed by a thief named Sakon who steals his mask. With his mask being stolen, he can no fulfill his vow to fuse his mask with Anju's. Ashamed, he goes into hiding. He finds out that the thief who stole his mask frequents a nearby shop that offers curiously magical goods. Kaffei decides he will spy on the shop. His goal is to follow Sakon back to his hideout and aquire his mask back so that he can fulfill his promise to Anju. This is where we come in. On a visit to the inn, Anju's mother mistakes you for a private investigator. Anju is an absolute wreck because Kaffei has been missing for days. Anju's mom hires you to figure out what has happened. After quite a bit of hunting and other various adventures, you finally catch up with Kaffei. He tells you the whole story of the vow and the theft and you agree to help him. He asks you to deliver a pendant to her that contains memories of their times together. With it there is also a letter, a new promise to Anju, if she will wait for him in her room at the inn on the eve of the Carnival of Time he will reunite with her and fulfill the covenant they made.(A little back story, the main antagonist in the game is making the moon fall slowly towards the earth. For the three days leading up to the Carnival of Time, it continues to fall. Many of the townsfolk have been evacuating still others don't think it's actually going to collide with the town so they stay.) So after delivering the letter and pendant, you and Kaffei spend the next 3 days trying to find Sakon's hideout. On the night of the final day you find the hideout and break in. But a trap has been placed. As soon as you get inside the mask starts moving on a sealed conveyor belt that leads to it's destruction. You and Kaffei have to work together to solve puzzle rooms to get to the end of the conveyor belt before the mask does. If you succeed in getting the mask, you and Kaffei race back to town to reunite with Anju. It is now approaching the dawn of the final day. The moon is falling very fast now. You and Kaffei get to the room where Anju has been waiting all night. Anju sees Kaffei and recognizes him even though he looks like a child. They embrace, and with you as their witness, they exchange their vows and fuse their mask into one. Then they hold one another, awaiting the imminent coming of dawn and the destruction of their town.\LF\LFIt's arguably the longest side story out of the entire Zelda franchise. There are a lot of things you have to do, and you're timed as well. There are several different ways to fail, and each way has it's own unique ending to the story. I just absolutely adore it.\LF\LFAnyway, the guy, Kaffei, has a mask that he wears when he goes into hiding. It's a mask that resembles the face of a mythological creature know as a Keaton. A Keaton is a wise yellow fox with many tails. I really want to dress up in Kaffei's attire and don a Keaton mask. Wow that ended up being a lot longer than I had anticipated.
So of course I love the story, but the fact that he hides behind the face of a fox makes me love it that much more.

I was expressing to my step-father that I had been receiving some feedback that I often have a "blank" expression which then is interpreted as a "bitch face" (those were the actual words spoken to me). He said he could kind of relate to the feedback because as he was getting to know me better there were times when he would come home and I would be occupied in some way (on my phone, reading, watching a movie, etc.) but the look on my face would convey a great sense of anger. So he would automatically assume I was angry with him and would avoid me for the rest of the night. But after getting to know me better, he was less hesitant to engage me in conversation, despite the look on my face, and came to discover that often I would be busy in the act of compartmentalizing things that were going through my head and in fact wasn't even angry at anything at all, least of all with him. So he said that he could understand why people would have that feedback for me, as uncool as that feedback is, but faulted the people giving me that feedback for not making  an effort to get to know me and understand me better so that they may then be able to understand the complete lack of anger on my part. He also said that he quickly realized that I am completely unaware that I have an angry look on my face when it's there. I'm actually more serious than anything. And it takes a whole lot to make me frustrated, let alone make me angry. I don't know of any more than a handful of times when something has actually made me angry, and even then, I'm able to reduce the anger to disappointment or frustration very quickly.
